===========================================================

When using this code please cite the paper:
S. Roy, A. Carass, amnd J.L. Prince, ``Magnetic Resonance Image
Example-Based Contrast Synthesis'', IEEE Trans. on Medical Imaging,
32(12):2348-2363, 2013.

http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpls/abs_all.jsp?arnumber=6600832

DOI: 10.1109/TMI.2013.2282126

===========================================================


If you do not have the Matlab Compiler Runtime v9.0 download it from
Mathworks:
https://www.mathworks.com/supportfiles/downloads/R2015b/deployment_files/R2015b/installers/glnxa64/MCR_R2015b_glnxa64_installer.zip

Unzip it and install it. Change the MCRROOT variable inside ``run_hallucination_v13d.sh" to the installed v90 directory




Example usage for regression:

./run_hallucination_v13d.sh testdata/regression/go03_spgr.nii,testdata/regression/go03_mprage.nii testdata/regression/as11_spgr.nii regression 1E5 150 0.01 3x3x3 12 0 0 0 0 testdata/regression/as11_synthmprage.nii 




Example usage for classification (To generate images like Fig 10 in the paper)

./run_hallucination_v13d.sh testdata/regression/go03_spgr.nii,testdata/classification/go03_3classseg.nii testdata/regression/as11_spgr.nii classification 1E5 150 0.01 3x3x3 12 0 0 0 0 testdata/classification/as11_exampleseg.nii 

